text: When getting a loan to build credit-he part where you have to add a bank for payment is dumb. This is my bank, I have no other bank to add and if I have to add another bank to my credit then I wouldn't need a money lion account and might as well close it. I missed several payments this way which only hurt my credit until after 4 chat attempts and 2 frustrating calls and after updating to the roar money account was i allowed to pay my loan payments. The chatbot should just have a live agent option when trying to get help along with the other options. Sometimes what I need is a simple question answered and the automated responses don't help in that case. Otherwise the moneylion concept is good, it's just the technical errors.

reply.message: We're sorry to hear about your experience with MoneyLion. We created Instacash to help you access extra money to cover everyday essentials and unexpected expenses, and we designed it to be easy to pay back. For these reasons, we allow you to take out Instacash in increments of $50 or less. Of course, if you’ve unlocked an Instacash limit higher than $50, it will all still be available to you if you need it. You’ll just have to take it out in advances of $50 at a time. We appreciate your feedback, and if you have any other questions, please feel free to contact us directly.

Pay what you think is fair, or don't pay at all, it's up to you. Just be sure to read the screens and make your selections carefully, and you can use Instacash without tips or fees if you choose. That said, if you choose to leave a tip — thank you! It helps us cover the costs of providing 0% APR cash advance to many, many folks like you!
